{% block content %}

	<h1>Guidelines for:</h1>
	<h2>The Bridgeport Hospital School of Nursing Alumnae Association I, Inc.<br>
	Nursing Education Scholarship</h2>

	<ol>
		<li>A recipient must be a current member of the BHSN Alumnae Association I, Inc.</li>
		<li>Scholarships are awarded only for degrees in nursing.</li>
		<li>The amount and number of scholarships to be awarded each year is to be decided by the board of the BHSN Alumnae Association I, Inc. </li>
		<li>Scholarship money will be awarded upon:
			<ul>
				<li>Proof of successful completion of the course (grade of C or better) by providing an official sealed or electronic transcript.</li>
				<li>Submission of university/college paid billing statement.</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Documentation of the amount of other scholarships, grants, and/or company reimbursement for the course being taken must be provided.</li>
		<li>Applications for the Nursing Education Scholarship must be submitted from January 15th through March 15th.</li>
		<li>Scholarships are awarded at the Bridgeport Hospital School of Nursing Alumnae Association I, Inc. Annual April Meeting/Banquet.</li>
		<li>Eligible courses are those completed during the past year from the previous Annual April Meeting/Banquet to the current Annual April Meeting/Banquet.</li>
		<li>Scholarships will be based on financial need and professional goals as presented in the application paragraph.</li>
	</ol>

	<p>Scholarship committee: Caren Silhavey (chairman), Edi Poidomani, Linda Podolak, Dottie Connelly, and Cathy Nucera.</p>

  <small>Updated April 2021</small>

